AS INTRODUCED
8
A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
9 to refer to the people for their approval or
rejection a proposed amendment to Section 8C of
10 Article X of the Constitution of the State of
Oklahoma; eliminating the limitation on the increase
11 of fair cash value of homesteads; providing certain
persons who own a homestead with exempt treatment
12 from all forms of ad valorem taxation; removing
limitation of fair cash value if improvements are
13 made; eliminating income requirement and definition;
providing ballot title; and directing filing.
14
15
16
17 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
18 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
19 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
20 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
21 the following proposed amendment to Section 8C of Article X of the
22 Constitution of the State of Oklahoma to read as follows:
23 SECTION 8C. A. Despite any provision to the contrary,
24 beginning January 1, 2005 2027, the fair cash value, as determined
Req. No. 15747 Page 1

1 by l aw, on each homestead of an individual head of household whose
2 gross household income from all sources for the preceding calendar
3 year did not exceed an amount as provided in subsection B of this
4 section, and which each individual head of household who is sixty-
5 five (65) years of age or older, shall not exceed the fair cash
6 value placed upon the property during the first year in which the
7 individual head of household was sixty-five (65) years of age or
8 older and had gross household income from all sources which did not
9 exceed an amount as provided in subsection B of this section.
10 Subject to the limitations of this section, the fair cash value
11 shall not exceed such amount as long as the individual head of
12 household who is sixty-five (65) years of age or older owns and
13 occupies the property and as long as the gross household income from
14 all sources does not exceed an amount as provided in subsection B of
15 this section. If any improvements are made to the property, the
16 fair cash value of the improvements shall be assessed in accordance
17 with law by the county assessor and added to the assessed value of
18 the property. Once the fair cash value of the improvements has been
19 added to the fair cash value of the property, the total fair cash
20 value shall not exceed the revised valuation of the property so long
21 as the individual head of household who is sixty-five (65) years of
22 age or older owns and occupies the property and so long as the gross
23 household income from all sources does not exceed an amount as
24 provided in subsection B of this section. For any individual head
Req. No. 15747 Page 2

1 of h ousehold who is sixty-five (65) years of age or older prior to
2 January 1, 1997, and has gross household income from all sources of
3 Twenty-five Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00) or less in calendar year
4 1996, the fair cash value of the real property shall be the fair
5 cash value placed upon the property on January 1, 1997. If the
6 individual head of household ceases to own and occupy the property
7 or if the gross household income from all sources exceeds an amount
8 as provided in subsection B of this section, the fair cash value of
9 the property shall be determined as if the provisions of Section 8
10 of Article X of the Constitution of the State of Oklahoma or any
11 other provisions relating to a limitation on the fair cash value of
12 locally assessed real property had been in effect during the time
13 the property was valued pursuant to the provisions of this section.
14 B. The income threshold for the gross household income from all
15 sources for an individual head of household under this section shall
16 not exceed the amount determined by the United States Department of
17 Housing and Urban Development to be the estimated median income for
18 the preceding year for the county or metropolitan statistical area
19 which includes such county. The Oklahoma Tax Commission shall
20 provide such information to each county assessor each year as soon
21 as such information becomes available be exempted from all forms of
22 ad valorem taxation on their homestead.
