Req. No. 15747 Page 3

1 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
2 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
3 the following form:
4 BALLOT TITLE
5 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
6 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
7 This measure amends Section 8C of Article 10 of the Oklahoma
8 Constitution. Increases in fair cash value of homesteads are
9 limited for individual heads of household age sixty-five (65) or
10 older. The increase cannot exceed the fair cash value of the
11 property during the first year in which the owner was sixty-five
12 (65) years of age or older. This limit applies if the
13 individual head of household meets both the age requirement and
14 an income limit determined by the United States Department of
15 Housing and Urban Development. This measure would eliminate the
16 limitation on the increase of the fair cash value. It would
17 provide head of households who are age sixty-five (65) and older
18 with exempt treatment from all forms of ad valorem taxation on
19 their homestead regardless of their income.
20 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
21 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
22 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
23 SECTION 3. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
24 immediately after the passage of this resolution, shall prepare and
Req. No. 15747 Page 4

1 file one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in
2 SECTION 2 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the
3 Attorney General.
